{"legislative_session": "20252026", "identifier": "SB982", "title": "Climate disasters: civil actions.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["Climatedisasters", "civilactions"], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "Existing law gives a person the right of protection from bodily harm and the right to possess and use property. If a person suffers bodily harm or a loss of their property because of the unlawful act or omission of another, existing law authorizes them to recover compensation from the person at fault, which is known as damages. Existing law authorizes the Attorney General to bring various civil actions due to damage or loss.\n\nThis bill would authorize the Attorney General to bring a civil action against a party responsible for climate-attributable damage to recover losses suffered by the California FAIR Plan Association, funds borrowed from the California Infrastructure and Economic Development Bank, or costs to insurance policyholders arising from a past climate disaster. The bill would make responsible parties strictly liable for any relief granted. The bill would create the Attorney General Climate Disaster Fund into which the monetary relief recovered by the Attorney General, excluding restitution, would be deposited, and would set forth specified uses for the account upon appropriation by the Legislature."}], "other_titles": [], "other_identifiers": [], "actions": [{"description": "Introduced. Read first time. To Com. on RLS. for assignment. To print.", "date": "2026-02-04", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": ["introduction", "reading-1"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "From printer. May be acted upon on or after March 7.", "date": "2026-02-05", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"upper\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Referred to Coms. on JUD. and INS.", "date": "2026-02-11", "organizat